.TH "sr_configure_minmax" 9 "sr_configure_minmax" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sr_configure_minmax \- Configures the SmartReflex to perform AVS using the minmaxavg module.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sr_configure_minmax
.BI "(struct omap_sr *sr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sr" 12
SR module to be configured.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This API is to be called from the smartreflex class driver to
configure the minmaxavg module inside the smartreflex module.
SR settings if using the ERROR module inside Smartreflex.
SR CLASS 3 by default uses only the ERROR module where as
SR CLASS 2 can choose between ERROR module and MINMAXAVG
module. Returns 0 on success and error value in case of failure.
